# Fixture FM8: TriG blank-node labels are scoped per graph block, not per
# document.
#
# Hypothesis: An implementation that uses a document-level blank-node label
# table (as Turtle does for its single implicit graph) will unify `_:b` from
# the default graph with `_:b` from the named graph, producing incorrect quads.
#
# Expected quads (four quads total):
#   DEFAULT_GRAPH:          _:b1 <http://example/p> <http://example/o1>
#   <http://example/g1>:    _:b2 <http://example/p> <http://example/o2>
# where _:b1 and _:b2 are DISTINCT blank nodes.
#
# Divergence signal: FactOnlyIn — if the implementation unifies the blanks,
# the triple in one graph may be attributed to the wrong blank node, causing
# the diff to see either a missing or extra fact.
#
# Spec: TriG §2.2 / §3 — "blank node identifiers are local to a graph."

{ _:b <http://example/p> <http://example/o1> . }
<http://example/g1> { _:b <http://example/p> <http://example/o2> . }
<http://example/g2> { _:b <http://example/p> <http://example/o3> .
                      _:b <http://example/q> <http://example/o4> . }
